This is how to next_smallest of lst:
   When lst's length is 0, then:
      The answer is []
   End when

   Remember that smallest is item 0 in lst
   Remember that i is 0

   Do this lst's length times:
      When item i in lst is less than smallest, then:
         Remember that smallest is item i in lst
      End when
      Increase i
   End do

   Remember that found is no
   Remember that next is 0
   Remember that i is 0

   Do this lst's length times:
      When item i in lst is more than smallest, then:
         When found is no, then:
            Remember that next is item i in lst
            Remember that found is yes
         But, if not:
            When item i in lst is less than next, then:
               Remember that next is item i in lst
            End when
         End when
      End when
      Increase i
   End do

   When found is yes, then:
      The answer is [next]
   But, if not:
      The answer is []
   End when
